# Project Conventions

Read `docs/ai/cap-coding-standards.md` for all coding standards, folder structure, and patterns.

## Key Rules

- Domain models in `db/`, services + thin handlers in `srv/`, logic in `srv/code/`, UI in `app/`
- Handler files (`srv/*.js`) are wiring only -- delegate to `srv/code/` modules
- Logic file naming: `<entity>-on-<action>-logic.js`, `<entity>-before-<event>-logic.js`
- Always use CQL (`SELECT`/`INSERT`/`UPDATE`/`DELETE`), never raw SQL
- Prefer CDS annotations over custom code
- Use `@sap-ai-sdk/foundation-models` for all LLM calls (see `docs/ai/sap-ai-sdk-guide.md`)

## MCP Tools

- **When unsure about CAP APIs**: use CDS MCP `search_docs` with your question
- **To inspect project CDS model**: use CDS MCP `search_model` with `projectPath: "/Users/soeren.leibach/Projects/insurance-fraud-detection"`
